title: My Three Favorite Sports
text:
1. Field Hockey

You get to run around and hit a ball
I made good friends
You get funny pictures of yourself (pardon the water mark)

title: My Three Favorite Sports
text:
2. Baseball

You get to run around and hit a ball
A lot of hand eye coordination involved
A lot of data to analyze
The Nationals do fireworks after their Friday night games
We (Yankees) got to steal this guy from the Nationals

title: My Three Favorite Sports
text:
3. Dance

I made a cool plot about the 5,6,7,8 count at the beginning of choreography:
If this slide was about dark matter, I would need this citation: Arkani-Hamed et al. (2009)



Here is the plot
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.plot([5, 6, 7, 8], [4, 3, 2, 1])
plt.title("Arbitrary Plot")
plt.xlabel("Dance Countoff")
plt.ylabel("Count(s) until dance begins")
plt.show()











Arkani-Hamed, Nima, Douglas P. Finkbeiner, Tracy R. Slatyer, and Neal Weiner. 2009. “A Theory of Dark Matter.” Phys. Rev. D 79 (January): 015014. https://doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevD.79.015014.
